#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`/frontend/admin-name-with-propagated-token`"
msgstr "`/frontend/admin-name-with-propagated-token`"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "When either `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token` or `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token` endpoint is called, `FrontendResource` uses a REST client with an OIDC client filter to get and propagate an access token to `ProtectedResource` ."
msgstr "Quando o endpoint `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token` ou `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token` é chamado, o `FrontendResource` usa um cliente REST com um filtro de cliente OIDC para obter e propagar um token de acesso para o `ProtectedResource`."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "When either `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` or `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` endpoint is called, `FrontendResource` uses a programmatically created OIDC client to get and propagate an access token to `ProtectedResource` by passing it to a REST client method as an HTTP `Authorization` header value."
msgstr "Quando o endpoint `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` ou `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` é chamado, o `FrontendResource` usa um cliente OIDC criado programaticamente para obter e propagar um token de acesso para o `ProtectedResource`, passando-o para um método de cliente REST como um valor do cabeçalho HTTP `Authorization`."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "When either `/frontend/user-name-with-propagated-token` or `/frontend/admin-name-with-propagated-token` endpoint is called, `FrontendResource` uses a REST client with `OIDC Token Propagation Filter` to propagate the current incoming access token to `ProtectedResource`."
msgstr "Quando o endpoint `/frontend/user-name-with-propagated-token` ou `/frontend/admin-name-with-propagated-token` é chamado, o `FrontendResource` usa um cliente REST com o `OIDC Token Propagation Filter` para propagar o token de acesso recebido no momento para o `ProtectedResource`."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`ProtectedResource` has two endpoints:"
msgstr "O `ProtectedResource` possui dois endpoints:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`/protected/user-name`"
msgstr "`/protected/user-name`"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`/protected/admin-name`"
msgstr "`/protected/admin-name`"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Both endpoints return the username extracted from the incoming access token, which was propagated to `ProtectedResource` from `FrontendResource`.\n"
"The only difference between these endpoints is that calling `/protected/user-name` is only allowed if the current access token has a `user` role, and calling `/protected/admin-name` is only allowed if the current access token has an `admin` role."
msgstr "Ambos os endpoints retornam o nome de usuário extraído do token de acesso recebido, que foi propagado para o `ProtectedResource` a partir do `FrontendResource`.\\nA única diferença entre esses endpoints é que a chamada para `/protected/user-name` só é permitida se o token de acesso atual tiver a role `user`, e a chamada para `/protected/admin-name` só é permitida se o token de acesso atual tiver a role `admin`."

