#. type: Title =
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, no-wrap
msgid "Writing the application"
msgstr "Escrevendo o aplicativo"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Implement `ProtectedResource`:"
msgstr "Implemente o `ProtectedResource`:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`ProtectedResource` returns a name from both `userName()` and `adminName()` methods.\n"
"The name is extracted from the current `JsonWebToken`."
msgstr "O `ProtectedResource` retorna um nome tanto nos métodos `userName()` quanto `adminName()`.\\nA nome é extraído do `JsonWebToken` atual."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Add the following REST clients:"
msgstr "Adicione os seguintes clientes REST:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`RestClientWithOidcClientFilter`, which uses an OIDC client filter provided by the `quarkus-rest-client-oidc-filter` extension to get and propagate an access token."
msgstr "`RestClientWithOidcClientFilter`, que usa um filtro de cliente OIDC fornecido pela extensão `quarkus-rest-client-oidc-filter` para obter e propagar um token de acesso."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam`, which accepts a token already acquired by the programmatically created OidcClient as an HTTP `Authorization` header value."
msgstr "`RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam`, que aceita um token já adquirido pelo OidcClient criado programaticamente como um valor do cabeçalho HTTP `Authorization`."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter`, which uses an OIDC token propagation filter provided by the `quarkus-rest-client-oidc-token-propagation` extension to get and propagate an access token."
msgstr "`RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter`, que usa um filtro de propagação de token OIDC fornecido pela extensão `quarkus-rest-client-oidc-token-propagation` para obter e propagar um token de acesso."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Add the `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` REST client:"
msgstr "Adicione o cliente REST `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter`:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Register an OIDC client filter with the REST client to get and propagate the tokens."
msgstr "Registre um filtro de cliente OIDC com o cliente REST para obter e propagar os tokens."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Add the `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` REST client:"
msgstr "Adicione o cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam`:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` REST client expects that the tokens will be passed to it as HTTP `Authorization` header values."
msgstr "O cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` espera que os tokens sejam passados a ele como valores do cabeçalho HTTP `Authorization`."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Add the `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` REST client:"
msgstr "Adicione o cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter`:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Register an OIDC token propagation filter with the REST client to propagate the incoming already-existing tokens."
msgstr "Registre um filtro de propagação de token OIDC com o cliente REST para propagar os tokens já existentes recebidos."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Do not use the `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` and `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` interfaces in the same REST client because they can conflict, leading to issues."
msgstr "Não use as interfaces `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` e `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` no mesmo cliente REST, pois elas podem entrar em conflito, causando problemas."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "For example, the OIDC client filter can override the token from the OIDC token propagation filter, or the propagation filter might not work correctly if it attempts to propagate a token when none is available, expecting the OIDC client filter to obtain a new token instead."
msgstr "Por exemplo, o filtro de cliente OIDC pode sobrescrever o token do filtro de propagação de token OIDC, ou o filtro de propagação pode não funcionar corretamente se tentar propagar um token quando nenhum estiver disponível, esperando que o filtro de cliente OIDC obtenha um novo token em vez disso."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Add `OidcClientCreator` to create an OIDC client programmatically at startup. `OidcClientCreator` supports `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` REST client calls:"
msgstr "Adicione o `OidcClientCreator` para criar um cliente OIDC programaticamente na inicialização. O `OidcClientCreator` suporta chamadas do cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam`:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`OidcClients` can be used to retrieve the already initialized, named OIDC clients and create new OIDC clients on demand."
msgstr "`OidcClients` pode ser usado para recuperar os clientes OIDC nomeados e já inicializados, e para criar novos clientes OIDC sob demanda."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Finish creating the application by adding `FrontendResource`:"
msgstr "Finalize a criação da aplicação adicionando o `FrontendResource`:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`FrontendResource` uses the injected `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` REST client with the OIDC client filter to get and propagate an access token to `ProtectedResource` when either `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token` or `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token` is called."
msgstr "O `FrontendResource` usa o cliente REST `RestClientWithOidcClientFilter` injetado com o filtro de cliente OIDC para obter e propagar um token de acesso para o `ProtectedResource` quando `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token` ou `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token` é chamado."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`FrontendResource` uses the injected `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` REST client with the OIDC token propagation filter to propagate the current incoming access token to `ProtectedResource` when either `/frontend/user-name-with-propagated-token` or `/frontend/admin-name-with-propagated-token` is called."
msgstr "O `FrontendResource` usa o cliente REST `RestClientWithTokenPropagationFilter` injetado com o filtro de propagação de token OIDC para propagar o token de acesso recebido no momento para o `ProtectedResource` quando `/frontend/user-name-with-propagated-token` ou `/frontend/admin-name-with-propagated-token` é chamado."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`io.quarkus.oidc.client.runtime.TokensHelper` is useful when the OIDC client is used directly, without the OIDC client filter.\n"
"Pass the OIDC client to `TokensHelper` to get the tokens.\n"
"`TokensHelper` acquires the tokens and refreshes them if necessary in a thread-safe way."
msgstr "`io.quarkus.oidc.client.runtime.TokensHelper` é útil quando o cliente OIDC é usado diretamente, sem o filtro do cliente OIDC. Passe o cliente OIDC para o `TokensHelper` para obter os tokens. O `TokensHelper` adquire os tokens e os renova se necessário de forma segura para threads (thread-safe)."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`FrontendResource` uses the programmatically created OIDC client to get and propagate an access token to `ProtectedResource` by passing it directly to the injected `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` REST client's method as an HTTP `Authorization` header value when either `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` or `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` is called."
msgstr "`FrontendResource` usa o cliente OIDC criado programaticamente para obter e propagar um token de acesso para o `ProtectedResource`, passando-o diretamente para o método do cliente REST injetado `RestClientWithTokenHeaderParam` como um valor de cabeçalho HTTP `Authorization` quando `/frontend/user-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` ou `/frontend/admin-name-with-oidc-client-token-header-param` é chamado."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Sometimes, an application needs to acquire tokens in a blocking manner before propagating them with the REST client.\n"
"This example shows how to acquire the tokens in such cases."
msgstr "Às vezes, uma aplicação precisa adquirir tokens de maneira bloqueante antes de propagá-los com o cliente REST. Este exemplo mostra como adquirir os tokens nesses casos."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Add a Jakarta REST `ExceptionMapper`:"
msgstr "Adicione um `ExceptionMapper` do Jakarta REST:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "This exception mapper is only added to verify during the tests that `ProtectedResource` returns `403` when the token has no expected role."
msgstr "Este mapeador de exceção é adicionado apenas para verificar durante os testes que o `ProtectedResource` retorna `403` quando o token não possui a role esperada."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-openid-connect-client.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Without this mapper, Quarkus REST (formerly RESTEasy Reactive) would correctly convert the exceptions that escape from REST client calls to `500` to avoid leaking the information from the downstream resources such as `ProtectedResource`.\n"
"However, in the tests, it would not be possible to assert that `500` is caused by an authorization exception instead of some internal error."
msgstr "Sem este mapeador, o Quarkus REST (anteriormente RESTEasy Reactive) converteria corretamente as exceções que escapam das chamadas do cliente REST para `500` para evitar o vazamento de informações dos recursos downstream, como o `ProtectedResource`. No entanto, nos testes, não seria possível afirmar que o `500` é causado por uma exceção de autorização em vez de algum erro interno."

